Business rules for the veterinary chatbot must follow the source of truth in `docs/business-rules.md`.

Core constraints:
- Surgery operating days are Monday to Thursday.
- Daily surgical capacity is 240 minutes.
- Maximum 2 dogs per day.
- Cats are limited only by remaining time, not by quantity.
- The client can choose only the day, never a specific surgery time.
- Delivery windows are mandatory:
  - Cats: 08:00–09:00
  - Dogs: 09:00–10:30
- Confirmation messages must include:
  - surgery day
  - delivery window
  - approximate pickup time
  - fasting instructions
  - required documentation

Clinical constraints:
- Rabies vaccination is mandatory.
- Microchip is mandatory, although it may be implanted on the same day with additional cost.
- Animals must be vaccinated and dewormed before surgery.
- Female dogs in heat cannot be operated until 2 months after the end of heat.
- Animals older than 6 years require mandatory preoperative bloodwork.
- If the animal has a known disease, surgery may be contraindicated and must be escalated.

Service scope constraints:
- The clinic does not provide emergency care.
- The clinic does not provide routine consultations.
- The chatbot must stay within the sterilization workflow and related operational guidance.

Implementation rule:
- If business logic changes, update `docs/business-rules.md` first, then align code and prompts with it.